The article is a work plan supporting the Communiqu√© of the Washington Nuclear Security Summit. It outlines the political commitments of participating states to carry out voluntary actions in relation to the storage, use, transportation, and disposal of nuclear materials, as well as preventing non-state actors from obtaining such materials for malicious purposes. The plan also emphasizes the importance of international conventions and agreements, such as the International Convention for the Suppression of Acts of Nuclear Terrorism and the Convention on the Physical Protection of Nuclear Material. It acknowledges the role of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) in providing guidance and recommendations for nuclear security measures and encourages member states to actively participate in implementing these measures. The plan also highlights the need for cooperation among states, international organizations, industries, and academia to enhance nuclear security, capacity building, and information sharing in order to detect and prevent illicit nuclear trafficking and nuclear terrorism.